; now it is entirely possible that it will survive and thrive and show movi=
es in movie theaters for decades to come because everyone went nuts and bou=
ght meme stocks this week.=E2=80=9D But that was not (just) passive luck on=
 AMC=E2=80=99s part; AMC saw the meme-stock movement and took full advantag=
e of it.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Lots of other people learned this lesson too, =
and for a while other companies =E2=80=94=C2=A0particularly companies that =
were struggling and did not have any obvious appeal to large fundamental in=
vestors =E2=80=94=C2=A0went around whispering =E2=80=9Cwait, can=C2=A0<em>w=
e=C2=A0</em>be a meme stock? Can=C2=A0<em>we=C2=A0</em>raise money at high =
prices by doing funny stuff on social media?=E2=80=9D Well, <a href=3D"http=
s://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34507057.283378/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuY=
mxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDQtMjQvYmVkLWJhdGgtbW92ZXMt=
aW50by10aGUtYmV5b25kP2NtcGlkPUJCRDAyMjgyNF9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1=
haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTI0MDIyOCZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW=
