scope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decorat=
ion: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #00000=
0; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">
some could</a>, but my sense is that the answer was=C2=A0<em>rarely=C2=A0</=
em>yes, that successfully pulling off a meme-stock investor relations strat=
egy requires (1) authentic spontaneous meme-stock interest from social medi=
a=C2=A0plus (2) authentic online engagement with the meme-stockers from=C2=
=A0management. Just saying =E2=80=9Clet=E2=80=99s be a meme stock=E2=80=9D =
doesn=E2=80=99t work.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I assume that there were several brief doomed =
efforts by public companies to become meme stocks, efforts that mostly died=
 in internal investor relations presentations or casual what-if emails from=
 CEOs. But probably some of them will end up in US Securities and Exchange =
Commission enforcement actions. <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusin=
ess.com/click/34507057.283378/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9uZXdzL3ByZXNzLXJlb=
GVhc2UvMjAyNC0yNg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB7190520c" itemprop=3D"StoryLink"=
 itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-de=
coration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #=
000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> Here=E2=80=99=
s one</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The Securities and Exchange Commission [Tuesda=
y]=C2=A0charged Paul A. Pereira, the former CEO and co-founder of Alfi, Inc=
., with making materially false and misleading statements on social media a=
bout the company=E2=80=99s financial and performance metrics in an attempt =
to boost the now defunct company=E2=80=99s stock price.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">According to the SEC's complaint, while servin=
g as the CEO of Alfi, a Florida-based advertising technology company, and u=
nder the pseudonym =E2=80=9CUptix12,=E2=80=9D Pereira allegedly posted shor=
tly after Alfi=E2=80=99s May 2021 initial public offering that he =E2=80=9C=
wouldn=E2=80=99t doubt=E2=80=9D that Alfi =E2=80=9Chas $10 mm to $20 mm in =
revenues already in their back pocket,=E2=80=9D when, in reality, the compa=
ny was set to report only $17,450 in revenue.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">From <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbus=
iness.com/click/34507057.283378/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9maWxlcy9saXRpZ2F=
0aW9uL2NvbXBsYWludHMvMjAyNC9jb21wLXByMjAyNC0yNi5wZGY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a2=
3cB464b61b8" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blan=
k" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom=
-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; back=
ground-color: #ccc;"> the complaint</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In the months following Alfi=E2=80=99s May 4, =
2021 IPO, the company received attention from members of the press and reta=
il investors on social media, who began to describe Alfi as a so-called =E2=
=80=9Cmeme stock.=E2=80=9D The term =E2=80=9Cmeme stock=E2=80=9D generally =
refers to equity securities that experienced extreme price volatility durin=
g the periods of 2020 and 2021 due, at least in part, to abnormally high vo=
lumes of buying and selling in the stock by retail investors. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Increasing Alfi=E2=80=99s visibility on social=
 media platforms with a large retail investor audience was a priority for P=
ereira. Pereira expressed concern to Alfi employees about the lack of atten=
tion being paid to Alfi on social media. He directed employees to post favo=
rable information about Alfi to social media platforms, such as Stocktwits,=
 a finance-focused social media platform popular among retail investors.</p=
>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On or around May 18, 2021, Pereira created an =
account on Stocktwits under the moniker =E2=80=9CUptix12.=E2=80=9D Over the=
 next five months, in violation of Alfi=E2=80=99s social media policy, Pere=
ira posted information on Stocktwits about Alfi multiple times per week and=
, often, multiple times per day.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Due to the pseudonymous nature of the =E2=80=
=9CUptix12=E2=80=9D moniker, which did not identify Pereira, there was no w=
ay for Stocktwits users to determine that Pereira, the CEO of Alfi at the t=
ime, controlled the Uptix12 account.=C2=A0Through the account, Pereira ofte=
n made posts praising=C2=A0Alfi=E2=80=99s technology and strategy and, at t=
imes, he disparaged other Stocktwits users who criticized Alfi.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On June 3, 2021, Pereira posted the following =
materially false and misleading statement on Stocktwits about Alfi=E2=80=99=
s reported revenues: =E2=80=9C$ALF Read between the CEO lines. Focused exec=
ution. They know exactly what they are doing. I wouldn=E2=80=99t doubt that=
 ALFI have [sic] $10 mm to $20 mm in revenues already in their back pocket!=
=E2=80=9D =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The day before his post, on June 2, 2021, Pere=
ira received a near final draft of Alfi=E2=80=99s first Form 10-Q, reportin=
g revenues of only $17,450 for the three-month period ending March 31, 2021=
. The final version of the Form 10-Q, filed with the Commission on June 10,=
 2021, also reported $17,450.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If you want people talking about your stock on=
 social media, one thing you can do is get on social media, start a pseudon=
ymous account, and start talking about your stock. The most straightforward=
 path to being a meme stock might be posting the memes yourself. I mean, I =
don=E2=80=99t think it=E2=80=99s all that likely to <em>work</em>, but it i=
s straightforward, and it=E2=80=99s no wonder that someone tried it. It jus=
t doesn=E2=80=99t seem that likely to me that the number of public company =
CEOs who were anonymously posting nice things about their companies on Stoc=
ktwits or Reddit in June 2021 was=C2=A0<em>one</em>.=C2=A0</p>
